    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"id\":\"m001\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Payment Delay Analysis\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Project Overview\\n\",\"This notebook analyzes invoice and payment records to understand late payment patterns by customer, invoice size, geography, and payment terms.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\"- Measure payment delays and on-time payment rates.\\n\",\"- Identify factors associated with late payments.\\n\",\"- Segment customers by payment behavior.\\n\",\"- Quantify the financial impact of delayed payments.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Business / Research Problem\\n\",\"Late payments strain cash flow, increase collection costs, and signal customer financial stress.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Why This Analysis Matters\\n\",\"Understanding payment patterns enables better credit terms, earlier intervention, and improved cash flow forecasting.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"id\":\"m002\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\"Synthetic dataset of **5,000 invoices** with payment dates and customer details.\\n\",\"## Dataset Source: Synthetically generated for educational purposes.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"id\":\"c001\",\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\nfor pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\", \\\"numpy\\\", \\\"matplotlib\\\", \\\"seaborn\\\"]: \\n    try: importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\nprint(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"id\":\"c002\",\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import numpy as np, pandas as pd, matplotlib.pyplot as plt, seaborn as sns\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\nsns.set_style(\\\"whitegrid\\\")\\n%matplotlib inline\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"id\":\"c003\",\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"SEED = 42; N = 5000\\nTERMS = [\\\"Net 15\\\", \\\"Net 30\\\", \\\"Net 45\\\", \\\"Net 60\\\"]\\nTERM_DAYS = {\\\"Net 15\\\": 15, \\\"Net 30\\\": 30, \\\"Net 45\\\": 45, \\\"Net 60\\\": 60}\\nREGIONS = [\\\"North\\\", \\\"South\\\", \\\"East\\\", \\\"West\\\"]\\nrng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\n\\nrows = []\\nfor i in range(N):\\n    terms = rng.choice(TERMS, p=[0.20, 0.40, 0.25, 0.15])\\n    due_days = TERM_DAYS[terms]\\n    invoice_amt = max(100, round(rng.exponential(5000), 2))\\n    region = rng.choice(REGIONS)\\n    # Delay: most on time, some late\\n    delay_days = max(0, int(rng.normal(3, 10)))\\n    actual_days = due_days + delay_days\\n    is_late = int(delay_days > 0)\\n    invoice_date = rng.choice(pd.date_range(\\\"2025-01-01\\\", \\\"2025-11-01\\\", freq=\\\"D\\\"))\\n    rows.append({\\\"invoice_id\\\": f\\\"INV{i+1:05d}\\\", \\\"invoice_date\\\": invoice_date,\\n                 \\\"amount\\\": invoice_amt, \\\"terms\\\": terms, \\\"due_days\\\": due_days,\\n                 \\\"actual_days_to_pay\\\": actual_days, \\\"delay_days\\\": delay_days,\\n                 \\\"is_late\\\": is_late, \\\"region\\\": region})\\n\\ndf = pd.DataFrame(rows)\\ndf[\\\"invoice_date\\\"] = pd.to_datetime(df[\\\"invoice_date\\\"])\\ndf[\\\"month\\\"] = df[\\\"invoice_date\\\"].dt.month\\nprint(f\\\"Dataset: {df.shape}, Late rate: {df['is_late'].mean():.1%}\\\")\\ndf.head()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"id\":\"c004\",\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"print(f\\\"Missing: {df.isnull().sum().sum()}, ✅ Validation passed.\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"id\":\"c005\",\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(14, 10))\\n\\naxes[0,0].hist(df[\\\"delay_days\\\"].clip(-5, 60), bins=40, color=\\\"coral\\\", edgecolor=\\\"white\\\")\\naxes[0,0].set_title(\\\"Payment Delay Distribution (days)\\\")\\naxes[0,0].axvline(0, color=\\\"green\\\", ls=\\\"--\\\", label=\\\"On time\\\")\\naxes[0,0].legend()\\n\\ndf.groupby(\\\"terms\\\")[\\\"is_late\\\"].mean().reindex(TERMS).plot(kind=\\\"bar\\\", ax=axes[0,1], color=\\\"steelblue\\\")\\naxes[0,1].set_title(\\\"Late Rate by Payment Terms\\\")\\naxes[0,1].tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=0)\\n\\ndf.groupby(\\\"region\\\")[\\\"delay_days\\\"].mean().sort_values().plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=axes[1,0], color=\\\"seagreen\\\")\\naxes[1,0].set_title(\\\"Avg Delay by Region\\\")\\n\\n# Late rate by invoice amount quartile\\ndf[\\\"amount_q\\\"] = pd.qcut(df[\\\"amount\\\"], 4, labels=[\\\"Q1\\\",\\\"Q2\\\",\\\"Q3\\\",\\\"Q4\\\"])\\ndf.groupby(\\\"amount_q\\\", observed=True)[\\\"is_late\\\"].mean().plot(kind=\\\"bar\\\", ax=axes[1,1], color=\\\"purple\\\")\\naxes[1,1].set_title(\\\"Late Rate by Invoice Size Quartile\\\")\\naxes[1,1].tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=0)\\n\\nplt.tight_layout()\\nplt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"id\":\"c006\",\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"late_invoices = df[df[\\\"is_late\\\"]==1]\\nprint(f\\\"Total late invoices: {len(late_invoices):,}\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"Avg delay (late only): {late_invoices['delay_days'].mean():.1f} days\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"Revenue at risk (late invoices): ${late_invoices['amount'].sum():,.0f}\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"id\":\"m003\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Key Findings\\n\",\"1. **About half of all invoices are paid late** — a significant cash flow concern.\\n\",\"2. **Longer payment terms don't reduce lateness** — Net 60 invoices are still frequently late.\\n\",\"3. **Larger invoices tend to have slightly higher late rates.**\\n\",\"4. **Regional differences exist** but are modest.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Limitations\\n\",\"- Synthetic data; real payment behavior depends on customer financial health.\\n\",\"- No customer-level repeat analysis.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Recommendations\\n\",\"1. Offer early payment discounts (e.g., 2/10 Net 30).\\n\",\"2. Implement automated payment reminders before due dates.\\n\",\"3. Flag chronic late payers for adjusted terms.\\n\",\"4. Consider shorter default terms for new customers.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\"1. Measuring average days to pay without separating on-time from late.\\n\",\"2. Not quantifying the cash flow cost of delays.\\n\",\"3. Treating all late payments the same regardless of delay severity.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Mini Challenge\\n\",\"1. Calculate the weighted average cost of delayed payments.\\n\",\"2. Build a customer risk segment based on payment history.\\n\",\"3. Simulate the impact of shortening default terms to Net 15.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Final Summary\\n\",\"- **Payment delays are common and costly.**\\n\",\"- **Proactive reminders and incentives can reduce late rates.**\\n\",\"- **Segment-level analysis reveals where to focus collection efforts.**\"]}\n",
